        "text": ", Septuagint. The Vulgate has here a distich which is not in the Hebrew, but a similar paragraph is found in the Septuagint. Thus Vulgate, \"In the abundance of righteousness virtue is greatest; but the imaginations of the wicked shall be rooted up;\" Septuagint, \"In the abundance of righteousness is much strength; but the impious shall be destroyed from the very root.\" The addition seems to have been an explanation of the following verse, which has been foisted into the text here. Proverbs 15:5",
